# GreenRoute — Web App

The React + Vite frontend for GreenRoute, wired to the GreenRoute API. Real login,
real persistence, every screen backed by the backend.

## Quickstart

Requires Node 18+ and the **GreenRoute API running** (see `greenroute-backend`).

```bash
npm install
npm run dev        # http://localhost:5173
```

Sign in with the demo account:

```
email:    owner@greenroute.app
password: greenroute
```

## Pointing at the API

By default the app calls `http://localhost:4000/api`. To change it, copy
`.env.example` to `.env` and set:

```
VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-host/api
```

## Build for production

```bash
npm run build      # outputs static files to dist/
npm run preview    # serve the built app locally
```

Deploy `dist/` to any static host (Netlify, Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, S3, nginx).
Set `VITE_API_URL` at build time so the bundle points at your deployed API, and
make sure the API's `CORS_ORIGIN` allows your frontend's URL.

## How it's wired

- `src/api.js` — the only place that talks to the backend. Holds the JWT in
  `localStorage`, attaches it as `Authorization: Bearer …`, and exposes one method
  per backend action. Swap the base URL here or via `VITE_API_URL`.
- `src/App.jsx` — auth gate and navigation. Three views: marketing site, login,
  and the app shell.
- `src/pages/*` — one file per screen. Each loads its own data through `api.js`,
  shows loading and error states, and updates from the server's response after
  every change (advance a job, optimize a route, send an invoice, log service).
- `src/ui.jsx` / `src/theme.js` — shared components and the design tokens.

